articles.description: Payton Pritchard had 19 points and 10 assists, and Troy Brown Jr. also had a double-double to lead Oregon past Washington State 84-57 on Sunday night.
articles.headline: Pritchard, Brown lead Oregon to 84-57 win over Washington St

articles.description: Shep Garner scored 16 points and Tony Carr had 15 points to lead Penn State to a 74-52 victory over Illinois on Sunday night.
articles.headline: Garner, Carr help Penn State beat Illinois 74-52

articles.description: After scoring a team-high 23 points, Grayson Allen credits the good ball movement to set him up in the Blue Devils' 80-69 win over the Yellow Jackets.
articles.headline: Allen credits ball movement for open looks

articles.description: Devin Davis scored 16 points, Armoni Brooks had a double-double and Houston throttled Tulane 73-42 on Sunday to stay in a tie for second place in the American Athletic Conference standings with Wichita State.
articles.headline: Houston dissects cold-shooting Tulane 73-42

videos.description: Carsen Edwards knocks in a couple of deep baskets in the first 5 minutes of the game against Wisconsin.
videos.headline: Edwards opens game with back-to-back triples for Purdue

videos.description: Dakota Mathias dishes to Matt Haarms who gets through a defender to hit a tricky layup and draws the contact.
videos.headline: Purdue's Haarms finishes tough and-1

videos.description: Vincent Edwards fakes the Wisconsin defender and dribbles all the way down the lane for a mean one-handed dunk in the first half.
videos.headline: Purdue's Edwards breaks through for slam

videos.description: Carsen Edwards finds Matt Haarms who rises up for a sweet two-handed dunk against Wisconsin.
videos.headline: Purdue's Edwards feeds Haarms for jam

videos.description: Vincent Edwards shows off a nice spin move and finishes at the rim with an easy dunk in the second half against Wisconsin.
videos.headline: Edwards twirls and throws it down for Purdue

videos.description: Ryan Cline knocks in a 3-pointer to extend the Boilermakers lead to 75-47 in the final minutes of the game against Wisconsin.
videos.headline: Purdue's Cline comes off bench for another nice triple

videos.description: The No. 3 Boilermakers start the game on an 18-2 run and don't look back, winning 78-50 against the Badgers.
videos.headline: Purdue steamrolls Wisconsin
